content: An array is a collection of items stored at contiguous memory locations. This is the simplest implementation of a data structure containing only a buffer and a length fixed variable.
New description for Circular Linked List
New description for Doubly Linked List
New description for Singly Linked List
The Skip List has not been implemented yet!
A Deque is a double-ended Queue.
A Deque Array is an implementation of a Deque using a buffer to store its data.
